Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.86,0:06:24.57,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\fnImpact\b1\fax-0.13\fsp3\frz7.351\pos(496,186)\c&H2B3B43&}Planetarium
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.05,0:06:27.76,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mitsuki-san. This says the show\N even has some Easter eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.76,0:06:30.35,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? \NWanna see who can find the most?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.35,0:06:32.94,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that sounds fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.32,0:06:35.29,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to try, too, Lemon?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.29,0:06:36.34,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Me, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.04,0:06:42.84,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,During the show, we'll give you and \NYanami-san some space. Go for it, bro.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.84,0:06:44.97,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Could you please not do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.97,0:06:46.76,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.76,0:06:50.12,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Lemon. \NThe three of us will watch it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.12,0:06:53.14,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuki, you should \Nwatch it with Asagumo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.38,0:06:56.10,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's all right. Why don't you join us?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.10,0:07:00.15,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to get to know \Nyou better, Yakishio-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.17,0:07:03.37,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.39,0:07:08.52,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,But really, Asagumo-san, \Nyou should watch it alone with Mitsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.69,0:07:09.03,Top,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.03,0:07:11.31,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Yana-chan! Nuk-kun! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.31,0:07:13.20,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second! I have a good reason—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.20,0:07:15.32,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.32,0:07:18.58,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,C'mon, you need to sit alone with Asagumo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.84,0:07:23.02,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,The three of us will watch it together. \NYou and Asagumo-san will watch it together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.02,0:07:25.26,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Good. That settles it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.93,0:07:41.94,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. Asagumo-san's your girlfriend. \NYou gotta put your girlfriend first!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.94,0:07:44.84,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah. I shouldn't have said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.84,0:07:49.87,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,No kidding! I mean, you're the guy I fell in love \Nwith once. Get your act together, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.65,0:07:51.89,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,I know, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.26,0:07:56.30,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,If he's such a great guy that Yakishio \Nfell in love with him, why isn't he more...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.35,0:07:59.29,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,In love?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.92,0:08:02.00,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.08,0:08:11.92,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Lemon, what do you mean, "fell in love"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.55,0:08:20.33,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uh, th-that was... n-no, I just meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.33,0:08:21.02,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.02,0:08:21.93,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,Lemon!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.76,0:08:25.86,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,Mitsuki-san, stop! Don't go!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.86,0:08:26.58,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.58,0:08:31.40,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,Please! I'm right here! \NAnd I'm your girlfriend!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.37,0:08:38.28,Default,Ayano,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.06,0:08:42.58,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Nukumizu-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.59,0:08:48.34,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't my style at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.34,0:08:49.63,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\b1\fs14\blur0.3\an8\c&H2E2F26&\pos(170,58)}Thank you \Nfor visiting
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.34,0:08:49.63,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\b1\fs12\blur0.3\an8\fscx80\c&H2E2F26&\pos(163.333,327.333)}Have a safe trip home
Dialogue: 1,0:08:48.96,0:08:51.01,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a role for a background character.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.08,0:08:56.89,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,But Yakishio...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.15,0:09:00.52,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,doesn't have a lead character \Nto chase after her.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.79,0:09:43.54,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna go ahead and take the bus home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.54,0:09:45.16,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,O-Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.06,0:09:50.03,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Can I at least wait with you\N until the bus comes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.03,0:09:54.51,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... Well, okay. Then talk to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.51,0:09:56.35,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.31,0:10:01.48,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,So, that club newsletter we're making... \NHave you decided what to write?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.48,0:10:03.35,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Nuk-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.35,0:10:08.05,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,At a time like this, shouldn't you try to cheer \Nthe girl up with a funny story or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.07,0:10:12.34,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,But I don't care. \NWe can talk about the newsletter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.34,0:10:15.10,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe I'll write a children's story.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.10,0:10:16.26,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,A children's story?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.26,0:10:17.19,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:22.60,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,A long, long time ago, in a place \Nfar away, there was a little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.30,0:10:29.19,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,The girl really loved to run. \NOne day, the girl met a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.21,0:10:33.75,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,The boy spent absolutely \Nall of his time reading books.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.72,0:10:39.17,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,The boy told the girl \Na whole lot about books.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.66,0:10:46.29,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,The two became friends, but it turned \Nout the boy was actually a prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.29,0:10:50.98,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,When the prince grew up, \Nhe would have to return to his castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.14,0:10:57.67,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,The girl wanted to go to the castle with him,\N but she didn't know proper etiquette,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.67,0:10:59.76,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,nor how to dance at the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.13,0:11:08.64,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,When the prince saw how sad the girl looked, \Nhe decided to teach her how to dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.54,0:11:12.47,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,The girl practiced as hard as she could.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.18,0:11:18.92,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,And then, it was decided that the girl \Ncould go to the castle with the prince.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.44,0:11:21.35,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,And they lived happily ever after.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.78,0:11:26.74,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord1.5\shad0\blur0.4\fs12\fscx90\b1\fsp1\an7\c&H2C2043&\3c&H615675&\pos(336,126)}Toyotetsu Bus
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.78,0:11:26.74,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\p1\bord0\shad0\blur0.5\fscx32\fscy20\an7\pos(350,206.5)\c&H0D2221&}m 0 0 l 100 0 100 100 0 100{\p0}
Dialogue: 1,0:11:22.78,0:11:26.74,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\fnArial\b1\fs8\fscx85\an8\pos(366,208.5)\c&H3D918C&}Now \NBoarding
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.31,0:11:27.56,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks. Could you say sorry\N to everyone for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.56,0:11:31.76,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the prince\N and the girl after that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.76,0:11:38.69,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,That was the whole thing. \NStories always end with "happily ever after."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.76,0:11:48.77,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,0)\b1\blur0.3\bord2\shad0\fs16\3c&HF2E7DD&\c&H615449&\pos(426,22)\frz9.113\frx6\fry10}Today
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.76,0:11:48.77,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,0)\b1\blur0.3\bord0\shad0\fs22\3c&HF2E7DD&\c&H615449&\frz7.568\pos(420.667,223.333)}Have you heard from Lemon at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:53.19,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,0)\b1\blur0.3\bord0\shad0\fs22\3c&HF2E7DD&\c&H615449&\frz4.835\pos(262.667,109.334)}Have you heard from Lemon at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:53.19,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,0)\b1\blur0.3\bord0\shad0\fs14\3c&HF2E7DD&\c&H615449&\frz4.835\pos(580.667,131.333)}PM
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:53.19,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,0)\b1\blur0.3\bord0\shad0\fs14\3c&HF2E7DD&\c&H615449&\frz4.835\pos(305.333,314.666)}PM
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.26,0:11:53.19,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,0)\b1\blur0.3\bord0\shad0\fs22\3c&HF2E7DD&\c&H26392D&\frz4.835\pos(454.667,252)}Not since that day
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.72,0:12:06.33,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize for contacting you this late.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.33,0:12:07.93,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,It's no trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.53,0:12:11.34,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,Did you get in touch with Yakishio-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.46,0:12:16.31,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,This is all because I wasn't \Nsure about my feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.31,0:12:17.07,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.03,0:12:23.53,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,When I said I'd step aside, it was just talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.02,0:12:29.56,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,But that day, I shouldn't have stopped \Nhim from chasing after Yakishio-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.56,0:12:32.49,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't think it's your fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.10,0:12:35.27,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so tired of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.48,0:12:42.23,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,If Mitsuki-san does actually like \NYakishio-san, I should break up with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.23,0:12:43.55,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.27,0:12:50.42,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,You weren't fooling around when you told \NAyano you had feelings for him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.42,0:12:51.48,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.67,0:12:58.55,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,If you two broke up because of this, \Nit'd hurt Yakishio more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.62,0:13:02.27,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.92,0:13:05.63,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I'm not trying to blame you for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.39,0:13:16.85,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnGeorgia\bord0\shad0\fscx90\fs12\blur0.5\an8\blur0.3\b1\c&HB8C9D7&\pos(208,24)}Yamasa\N Chikuwa
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.39,0:13:16.85,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord2\shad0\b1\fnArial\fscx85\blur0.5\fs14\3c&HF5FDFB&\c&HA2B2AD&\frz357.1\pos(431.334,46.667)}Higashihatcho
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.93,0:13:13.65,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,For now, would you let me deal with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.11,0:13:16.85,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,All right. But at least let me use this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.85,0:13:20.18,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,No, you definitely can't use that.\N Promise me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.01,0:13:21.79,Default,Chihaya,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.49,0:13:27.16,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,You promised, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.39,0:13:39.80,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.80,0:13:41.98,Italics,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening. Are you up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.98,0:13:43.46,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Uh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.46,0:13:47.44,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about Yakishio-chan. \NThat must've been rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.44,0:13:49.74,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, it was kind of a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.74,0:13:55.18,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,So listen. Right now, Yakishio-chan is \Nat her grandmother's house in Shinshiro.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.18,0:13:57.93,Italics,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure you're free tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:02.15,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Um, hold on, Senpai. I'm not sure \NI understand what's going on here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.52,0:14:07.01,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,It's obvious, isn't it? We're all going \Ntogether to get Yakishio-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.16,0:14:18.49,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck am I doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.46,0:14:20.71,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,300)\bord0\shad0\blur0.4\fs12\fay-0.03\c&H171C09&\pos(354,313)}Mokkulu Shinshiro
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.74,0:14:20.73,Default,Mother,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.73,0:14:22.09,Default,Kid,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.09,0:14:23.46,Default,Mother,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's go eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:34.85,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\fscx85\fs14\bord1.2\fax-0.02\shad1\3c&H597476&\frz2.932\pos(362,91.333)\4c&H333D45&}Stone-Roasted Frankfurters
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.88,0:14:34.85,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnArial Black\fscx85\fs17\bord1.2\fax-0.02\shad1\sn3\3c&H162025&\frz2.932\4c&H080E10&\pos(530,106.667)\c&H7A858C&}Goheimochi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.54,0:14:31.64,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking a lot \Nabout sugar recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.64,0:14:33.93,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah? You've been thinking, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.93,0:14:36.80,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Sure have. About 10,000 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.80,0:14:40.70,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,humans shifted from hunting and gathering \Nto an agriculture-based lifestyle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.70,0:14:44.25,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,That essentially means they shifted\N to a sugar-based lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.25,0:14:47.94,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, it does? Is there much left to this story?
Dialogue: 1,0:14:47.94,0:14:51.96,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be an exaggeration to say\N that humans are slaves to sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs11\an8\bord2\b1\fay0.03\blur0.4\shad0\3c&HF8FCFC&\c&H96ADAA&\move(-4,100,105,110)}Supersized\N Goheimochi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs10\an8\bord2\b1\fay0.03\fax-0.07\blur0.4\shad0\3c&HF8FCFC&\c&H96ADAA&\move(78.667,124,187.667,134)}Goheimochi
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs7.5\an8\bord2\b1\fay0.04\fax-0.09\blur0.4\shad0\3c&HDDDCCA&\c&H6B6759&\move(157.333,127.333,254.333,137.333)}Extra Coarse Ground\NStone-Roasted \NFrankfurter
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs6\an8\bord2\b1\fay0.04\fax-0.09\blur0.4\shad0\3c&HDDDCCA&\c&H6B6759&\move(225.667,130.667,319.667,140.667)}Extra Coarse Ground \NStone-Roasted \NFrankfurter \NHalf Size
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs5.5\an8\bord2\b1\fay0.04\fax-0.09\blur0.4\shad0\3c&HDDDCCA&\c&H6B6759&\move(287.333,136.667,376.333,146.667)}Extra Coarse Ground\N Stone-Roasted \NCheese \NFrankfurter
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs5\an8\bord2\b1\fay0.04\fax-0.09\blur0.4\shad0\3c&HB5BFA9&\c&H6B6759&\move(346,140,431,146)}Extra Coarse Ground \NStone-Roasted \NSpicy \NFrankfurter
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs9\an8\bord2\b1\fay0.04\fax-0.09\blur0.4\shad0\3c&HA2B1A4&\c&H435852&\move(395.333,139,476.333,146)}Bacon \NBlock \NSkewer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs4.55\an8\bord2\b1\fay0.04\fax-0.09\blur0.4\shad0\3c&H7B908D&\c&H2C3B37&\move(442.967,148.333,521.667,151.333)}Extra Coarse Ground \NStone-Roasted \NSuper Long \NFrankfurter
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs10\an8\bord2\b1\fay-0.07\fax-0.07\blur0.4\shad0\3c&HF8FCFC&\c&H96ADAA&\move(64.333,262,170.333,264)}5-Pack \NGoheimochi \Nw/ Walnut Sauce
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.07,0:14:58.54,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fs9\an8\bord2\b1\fay-0.08\fax-0.07\blur0.4\shad0\3c&HF8FCFC&\c&H96ADAA&\move(138.333,265.333,242.333,261.333)}Goheimochi\N & Frankfurt Set
Dialogue: 1,0:14:51.96,0:14:57.50,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,So I think the time has come for me to \Nreevaluate my relationship with sugar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.50,0:14:58.54,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,So basically...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.96,0:15:00.58,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,You ate too much somen and gained wei—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.58,0:15:02.25,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,I have not gained weight!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.25,0:15:07.17,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Your Yanami-chan, for the 15th time and the \Nfirst in a year, has achieved her perfect body!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.29,0:15:10.72,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,I really believe plum jam is on the left.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.72,0:15:13.85,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,N-No. Plum jam is on the r-right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.85,0:15:17.33,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like deer curry\N is on the left, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.33,0:15:20.85,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,The sourness of plum jam makes it taste\Nlike it's never had a naughty side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.38,0:15:26.19,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's exactly why it goes on \Nthe right. It's a generational shift.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.19,0:15:28.35,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world are you two doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.35,0:15:31.68,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Nukumizu-kun. It appears \Nyou require an explanation!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.68,0:15:32.92,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,No, I really don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.92,0:15:34.66,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Just listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.66,0:15:38.34,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Decadent BL fans of the world \Ncan look at a pencil and an eraser
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.87,0:15:37.12,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(270,0)\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\b1\fscx90\fs10\c&H202D35&\pos(500,215.333)\frz355.5}Plum Jam
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.12,0:15:37.24,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\b1\fscx90\fs10\c&H202D35&\pos(515.333,214.667)\frz353.7}Plum Jam
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.24,0:15:37.37,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\b1\fscx90\fs10\c&H202D35&\pos(524,214)\frz351.2}Plum Jam
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.24,0:15:37.37,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{3\bord2.5\shad0\blur0.3\fs16\fnArial Black\3c&H74A7BF&\c&H14056E&\pos(164.667,260)\frz15.76}Spicy
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.37,0:15:39.75,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\b1\fscx90\fs10\c&H202D35&\frz351.2\pos(532,212.667)}Plum Jam
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.37,0:15:39.75,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{3\bord2.5\shad0\blur0.3\fs16\fnArial Black\3c&H74A7BF&\c&H14056E&\frz17.5\pos(146.667,214)}Spicy
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.34,0:15:42.71,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,and assign one as the top and the other as the \Nbottom. That kind of prejudice is spreading.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.71,0:15:44.71,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that exactly what you were doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.02,0:15:48.80,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,It's merely a thought experiment. \NA kind of intellectual training.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.80,0:15:52.48,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,So what was all that stuff \Nabout "right" and "left"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.61,0:15:52.72,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\fnArial\b1\c&H212527&\pos(385.333,296)\frz356.1}Top & Bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.72,0:15:52.84,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\fnArial\b1\c&H212527&\frz357.7\pos(388.667,254.667)}Top & Bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.84,0:15:58.35,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\fnArial\b1\c&H212527&\pos(398,214)}Top & Bottom
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.11,0:15:56.36,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,When you write it horizontally\N as "top and bottom,"
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.36,0:15:58.62,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,"top" is on the left, yes?
Dialogue: 1,0:15:58.62,0:16:01.77,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,That means left represents the top, \Nand right represents the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.72,0:15:59.85,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\b1\fscx90\fs9\c&H202D35&\frz346.7\pos(408,283.333)}Plum Jam
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.85,0:16:04.81,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\b1\fscx90\fs9\c&H202D35&\pos(380,198.667)\frz6.607}Plum Jam
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.73,0:16:01.85,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{3\bord2.5\shad0\blur0.3\fs16\fnArial Black\3c&H74A7BF&\c&H14056E&\frz17.5\pos(166.667,306.667)}Spicy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.77,0:16:04.81,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This way, we can have debates \Neven with people around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.85,0:16:04.81,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{3\bord2.5\shad0\blur0.3\fs16\fnArial Black\3c&H74A7BF&\c&H14056E&\frz17.5\pos(164,264)}Spicy
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.81,0:16:06.27,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,That doesn't mean you should!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.63,0:16:09.40,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,But calling the spicy one \Nthe top feels like a cop-out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.40,0:16:12.74,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,C-C-Curry's passionate spiciness \Ncould i-injure his partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.74,0:16:15.16,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(300,0)\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\b1\fscx90\fs18\c&H202D35&\pos(506.667,172)}Plum Jam
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.18,0:16:15.16,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's the reason!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.16,0:16:16.67,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,I get it now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.67,0:16:21.65,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,He's so desperate to ravish him, it could \Ncause an injury, so he can't even touch him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.00,0:16:24.08,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my God! That is so hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.48,0:16:29.05,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,So, um, do you think we should be on our way?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.12,0:16:35.05,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Are we really on our way to Yakishio's place?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.54,0:16:38.02,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,We keep going deeper into the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.02,0:16:40.68,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing to worry about. \NGPS will get us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.68,0:16:42.80,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I hope it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.48,0:16:46.62,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,But how did you know she was \Nat her grandmother's place?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.96,0:16:50.78,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, Yakishio-chan has \Nbeen skipping track practice, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.78,0:16:55.61,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,The president talked to me, and we both \Nwent to see Yakishio-chan's mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.39,0:17:00.14,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Her mom was worried \Nabout how she was doing, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.89,0:17:05.09,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,And we've arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.92,0:17:06.60,Italics Top,car navigation,0000,0000,0000,,You have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.22,0:17:11.05,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way the Yakishio clan\N lives in a place like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.52,0:17:14.05,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, we got kind of lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.44,0:17:17.12,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Could you give me the address one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.18,0:17:21.47,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. Okay, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.47,0:17:23.60,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Nukumizu-kun, that's the bridge!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.97,0:17:25.27,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stand over there,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.27,0:17:29.18,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,so take a grammable pic of me from \Ndownstream and try not to get swept away!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.18,0:17:32.32,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you don't mind your \Nphone getting swept away with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.28,0:17:37.58,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Nukumizu-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.58,0:17:38.96,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, Komari?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.58,0:17:38.96,Top,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.96,0:17:42.49,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Shh! I s-saw a r-river crab.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.49,0:17:45.11,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, a river crab? Where was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.11,0:17:48.42,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't talk too much or it won't come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.17,0:17:52.55,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing, \Nmaking me pose for nothing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.47,0:17:56.97,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Are you really that into river crabs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.97,0:17:58.08,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Th-There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.51,0:17:59.66,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Crabby.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.79,0:18:02.42,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Komari-chan's crabby, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.84,0:18:05.38,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Do you guys really love crabs that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.38,0:18:05.93,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.93,0:18:08.15,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Is it 'cause they taste good?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.15,0:18:11.90,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, don't be so grumpy. \NLet's take a video. A video.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.90,0:18:15.63,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nice idea. You're starting to get it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.44,0:18:20.76,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.76,0:18:25.50,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,When you put me on the spot and tell me to \Nmove around, I kinda don't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.50,0:18:28.20,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Why not sing something? \NThe Mr. Elephant song?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.20,0:18:32.44,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that be sad, though? Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.26,0:18:38.55,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? Did you see a \Nking crab this time? Or a snow crab?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.55,0:18:41.43,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, it's something even rarer.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.43,0:18:43.43,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Really? A horsehair crab?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.09,0:18:59.71,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen a real \Nclawfoot bathtub before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.71,0:19:02.66,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,I guess it used to be \Nsomebody's vacation home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.66,0:19:06.72,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Grandma said she bought it \Nwhen she was a college professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.33,0:19:11.29,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,An ex-college professor's vacation home!\N Hey, can I take a picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.52,0:19:13.25,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Can I drop hints?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.25,0:19:14.25,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Hints?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.70,0:19:17.36,Top,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "drop hints"?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.05,0:19:19.09,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we met up with Yakishio, \Nbut what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.09,0:19:23.30,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,What do we do? \NShe seems okay, so isn't that enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.55,0:19:28.47,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,That's what I mean. If she was open \Nabout being depressed, that'd be one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.03,0:19:32.55,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,but when she's acting so cheery, \Nit makes it harder to bring it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.73,0:19:37.97,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,You have a really bad habit of \Nalways trying to rush to conclusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.23,0:19:44.97,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Acting cheery is one way to get cheery. \NJust keep her company for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.43,0:19:47.75,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, Komari-chan. You're up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.75,0:19:48.49,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.90,0:19:52.96,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,I-I don't have any sore muscles!\N Senpai, wait! Stop—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.36,0:19:52.96,Top,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.84,0:20:02.30,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Thi-i-is fe-e-els so-o go-o-od.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.24,0:20:05.30,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,So what were you guys doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.30,0:20:09.12,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,We just... randomly came to hang out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.12,0:20:10.02,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,No, you didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.02,0:20:12.04,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, well, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.45,0:20:15.70,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, though. For looking out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.98,0:20:19.15,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.70,0:20:21.56,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, do we have guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.56,0:20:24.37,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Welcome back, Grandma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.76,0:20:27.06,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Please excuse the intrusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.51,0:20:31.01,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,We're members of the literature \Nclub at Lemon-san's school.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.01,0:20:34.36,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you. \NPlease make yourselves at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.36,0:20:38.33,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes! Wouldn't this be \Na good time to order sushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.33,0:20:40.34,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything you kids can't eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.34,0:20:43.01,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, we couldn't impose \Non you for something like—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.30,0:20:49.76,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,We're all good! We can eat anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.76,0:20:52.14,Default,all,0000,0000,0000,,Let's eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.14,0:20:53.69,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,Let's.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.27,0:20:58.65,Default,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,The fish is so tender and delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.22,0:21:00.30,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,How is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.30,0:21:03.27,Top,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,This really is delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.98,0:21:03.28,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,You should hurry up and eat, too, Komari.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.86,0:21:06.24,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,The sushi's disappearing \Nfaster than I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.24,0:21:09.08,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,I-I've never had salmon roe before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.33,0:21:10.96,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,I'm kinda scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.96,0:21:13.29,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you should leave them be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.29,0:21:16.25,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Here, Komari-chan. Eat these.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.25,0:21:17.67,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,It's sea urchin and abalone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.67,0:21:21.12,Default,Komari,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. N-Never had either one before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.27,0:21:23.88,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Let's clean up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.88,0:21:24.92,Default,all,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.49,0:21:26.93,Top,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wipe the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.93,0:21:30.01,Top,Anna,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Then I'll take this stuff away.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.38,0:21:31.42,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Do you ever get lonely \Nliving alone in the mountains?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.42,0:21:34.60,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,I have the internet these days, so I get by.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.89,0:21:38.60,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,And my granddaughter is thoughtful\N enough to brings guests over.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.26,0:21:41.07,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.07,0:21:45.03,Default,Lemon,0000,0000,0000,,You should all spend the night.\N We have tons of rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.27,0:21:49.49,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate the offer, but I didn't \Nbring a change of clothes or anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.18,0:21:51.23,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Wait just a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.62,0:21:55.83,Italics,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Yanami changed into something different \Nafter falling into the river, didn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.72,0:22:02.73,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai, were you actually planning \Nto stay over from the start?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.10,0:22:05.55,Default,Koto,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.55,0:22:07.23,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't hear anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.76,0:22:10.33,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,But it'd be rude to just \Nbarge in on them like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.33,0:22:13.80,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it's fine. I'd be very happy \Nto host all of you tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.80,0:22:15.40,Default,Nukumizu,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.40,0:22:17.98,Default,Grandma,0000,0000,0000,,Just let Grandma take care of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.24,0:22:29.99,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.5\fs26\fnGeorgia\pos(320,65)\c&HE9E9E9&\t(0,400,\c&HB2B1B5&)\t(400,800,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)\t(800,1200,\c&HB2B1B5&\blur0.3)\t(1200,1600,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)\t(1600,2000,\c&HB2B1B5&\blur0.3)\t(2000,2400,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)\t(2400,2800,\c&HB2B1B5&\blur0.3)\t(2800,3200,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)\t(3200,3600,\c&HB2B1B5&\blur0.3)\t(3600,4000,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)}Episode 6
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.24,0:22:29.99,Default,text,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.5\fs25\an8\fnGeorgia\c&HE9E9E9&\t(0,400,\c&HB2B1B5&)\t(400,800,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)\t(800,1200,\c&HB2B1B5&\blur0.3)\t(1200,1600,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)\t(1600,2000,\c&HB2B1B5&\blur0.3)\t(2000,2400,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)\t(2400,2800,\c&HB2B1B5&\blur0.3)\t(2800,3200,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)\t(3200,3600,\c&HB2B1B5&\blur0.3)\t(3600,4000,\c&HE9E9E9&\blur0.9)\pos(320,285)}Let Any One of You Who Has Never Been Dumped \NBe the First to Throw a Stone at the Losing Heroine
